title: Carmen I'm Too Bizet
description: After Ricky's friend leaves her baby at the café, so she can go on a date, Ricky is left to look after her when Jim and Memo go to a Soccer match.

title: Shakespeare Was a Greek
description: After Jim and Liz watch a Shakespeare play, Jim decides to make his own version of Shakespeare at the café.

title: Ricky Sings the Blues
description: When Ricky's old friend comes to the café, Ricky has a decision to make; to re-join the Jazz band or to stay at the café.

title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Greeks
description: Memo's friend, the famous soccer star Danny O'Brien, comes to town. He wants to hook his sister up with Danny. So they go on a date to an "Italian" restaurant where hijinks ensue.

title: Back in the U.S.S.R
description: When Liz brings a Russian exchange student to the café, Jim is convinced that he is a spy.

title: Acropolis Law
description: After Sophie accidentally messes up Effie's hair, Effie believes that it was done on purpose.

title: Confessions of a Hair Gel Goddess
Here Come the Brides: Part One
description: Jim struggles to hide the fact that he has planned to weddings; one with Suzzana and the other with Julia.

title: Here Come the Brides: Part Two
description: After Jim proposes to both Suzzana and Julia, he proceeds to plan a wedding for each but fails to show up to either of them.
